{
  "texts": [
    "The database interface module contains SQL code written and optimized for Oracle, since it has historically been the main database technology.",
    "When using a PostgreSQL database, queries are translated to the PostgreSQL dialect through an in-house layer.The database usage has been highly optimized to keep up with the transaction rate required by big science experiments.",
    "In addition to the usage of targeted indexes, Oracle partitioning is also used to optimize data access.",
    "Depending on the size and relevance of the tables, older entries can be deleted through a sliding window procedure.",
    "However, for many tables the information is kept over extended periods of time in order to be able to browse the data in the monitoring."
  ]
}